===2000===
As of the [[census]]<ref name="GR2">{{cite web|url=https://www.census.gov |publisher=[[United States Census Bureau]] |access-date=2008-01-31 |title=U.S. Census website }}</ref> of 2000, there were 1,143 people, 422 households, and 281 families residing in the CDP.  The population density was {{convert|2,813.3|PD/sqmi|PD/km2|sp=us|adj=off}}.  There were 530 housing units at an average density of {{convert|1,304.5|/sqmi|/km2|sp=us|adj=off}}.  The racial makeup of the CDP was   55.3% of the population were [[Race (United States Census)|Hispanic]] / [[Race (United States Census)|Latino]] of any race, 54.8% [[Race (United States Census)|White]], 3.2% [[Race (United States Census)|Black]] or [[Race (United States Census)|African American]], 2.0% [[Race (United States Census)|Native American]], 4.6% [[Race (United States Census)|Asian]], 28.1% from [[Race (United States Census)|other races]], and 7.4% from two or more races.

There were 422 households, out of which 33.6% had children under the age of 18 living with them, 39.3% were [[Marriage|married couples]] living together, 18.2% had a female householder with no husband present, and 33.4% were non-families. 29.1% of all households were made up of individuals, and 14.7% had someone living alone who was 65 years of age or older.  The average household size was 2.7 and the average family size was 3.3.

In the CDP, the population was spread out, with 30.0% under the age of 18, 8.0% from 18 to 24, 24.0% from 25 to 44, 22.4% from 45 to 64, and 15.6% who were 65 years of age or older.  The median age was 36 years. For every 100 females, there were 100.2 males.  For every 100 females age 18 and over, there were 105.7 males.

The median income for a household in the CDP was $25,592, and the median income for a family was $27,500. Males had a median income of $36,786 versus $26,250 for females. The [[per capita income]] for the CDP was $11,297.  About 15.1% of families and 21.4% of the population were below the [[poverty line]], including 19.8% of those under age 18 and 12.4% of those age 65 or over.

===2010===
The [[2010 United States census]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.census.gov/2010census/popmap/ipmtext.php?fl=06:0651392|archive-url=https://archive.today/20140715032004/http://www.census.gov/2010census/popmap/ipmtext.php?fl=06:0651392|url-status=dead|archive-date=July 15, 2014|title=2010 Census Interactive Population Search: CA – Niland CDP|publisher=U.S. Census Bureau|access-date=July 12, 2014}}</ref> reported that Niland had a population of 1,006. The population density was {{convert|2,504.8|PD/sqmi|PD/km2|sp=us|adj=off}}. The racial makeup of Niland was 539 (53.6%) [[White (U.S. Census)|White]], 36 (3.6%) [[African American (U.S. Census)|African American]], 20 (2.0%) [[Native American (U.S. Census)|Native American]], 36 (3.6%) [[Asian (U.S. Census)|Asian]], 0 (0.0%) [[Pacific Islander (U.S. Census)|Pacific Islander]], 315 (31.3%) from [[Race (United States Census)|other races]], and 60 (6.0%) from two or more races. There were 618 [[Hispanic (U.S. Census)|Hispanic]] or [[Latino (U.S. Census)|Latino]] residents, of any race (61.4%).

The Census reported that 1,006 people (100% of the population) lived in households, 0 (0%) lived in non-institutionalized group quarters, and 0 (0%) were institutionalized.

There were 367 households, out of which 131 (35.7%) had children under the age of 18 living in them, 143 (39.0%) were [[marriage|opposite-sex married couples]] living together, 83 (22.6%) had a female householder with no husband present, 30 (8.2%) had a male householder with no wife present.  There were 25 (6.8%) [[POSSLQ|unmarried opposite-sex partnerships]], and 5 (1.4%) [[same-sex partnerships|same-sex married couples or partnerships]]. 99 households (27.0%) were made up of individuals, and 49 (13.4%) had someone living alone who was 65 years of age or older. The average household size was 2.74.  There were 256 [[family (U.S. Census)|families]] (69.8% of all households); the average family size was 3.27.

The population dispersal was 248 people (24.7%) under the age of 18, 99 people (9.8%) aged 18 to 24, 215 people (21.4%) aged 25 to 44, 284 people (28.2%) aged 45 to 64, and 160 people (15.9%) who were 65 years of age or older.  The median age was 39.6 years. For every 100 females, there were 96.9 males.  For every 100 females age 18 and over, there were 94.4 males.

There were 489 housing units at an average density of {{convert|1,217.5|/sqmi|/km2|sp=us|adj=off}}, of which 367 were occupied, of which 189 (51.5%) were owner-occupied, and 178 (48.5%) were occupied by renters. The homeowner vacancy rate was 7.4%; the rental vacancy rate was 23.3%.  497 people (49.4% of the population) lived in owner-occupied housing units and 509 people (50.6%) lived in rental housing units.

